article.headline: Quinnipiac 85, Dartmouth 63
article.story: HAMDEN, Conn. (AP) -- DeMario Anderson scored 27 points Wednesday night to lead Quinnipiac to an 85-63 win over Dartmouth. The Bobcats (5-5) took control early, pulling away from 7-7 tie with quick 18-0 run. Quinnipiac hit seven straight shots including four three-pointers in the spurt. The Bobcats finished the first half 15-27 from the floor and hit all seven free throw attempts for a 43-25 lead at the break. James Feldeine scored nine straight Quinnipiac points in the second half to help the Bobcats open up a 56-37 lead. Feldeine finished with 11 points, all in the second half. Casey Cosgrove was 4-for-4 from three-point range and finished with 12 points as did guard Bryan Geffen. The two combined for 17 assists. Alex Barnett led Dartmouth (5-5) with 17 points.
